      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"2. TUAHIWI filled the minor placings again last time when second (22.65) at Ascot Park, making it three straight minors on end. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of three starts. Well placed here and can go close with a clear run. 3. RIPSLINGER RIOT has been hard to follow lately, running fourth (17.31) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at this track. Well placed here and should do much better. 8. HOMEBUSH LEO comes off an average effort last start when fifth at Ascot Park over 390m behind Skeletor (22.98) in a Class 3/4. Wide draw is ideal and shapes as one to consider. 6. ANOTHER LOVE drops in trip and cannot be left out. Has more ability than recent form reads on paper.\",\"runners\":[2,3,8,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
